The current Work Plan aims to orient the MDG reporting process with the following major deliverables:

1. Production and launching of the 3rd MDG Report;

2. Support upstream pro-poor policy formulation and MDG based planning so that MDGs be fully integrated in the national planning process;

3. The capacity building to monitor the efforts towards MDGs achievement. This includes the provision of support for undertaking analytical studies on related topics;

4. The strengthening of Government capacity for coordination, management and harmonization of external support, reducing transaction costs and increasing levels of efficiency in its use; 

5. The building of organizational capacity of CSO to play a more proactive role in the development discourse, through their participation in poverty policy evaluations, service delivery and in the analysis of the proposed plans and data monitoring at central and provincial levels; 

6. The strengthening of national statistical capacity, especially to better inform on human and MDGs development, through needs assessment and implementation of a Capacity Development strategy at National Statistics System.
